This package contains code for evaluating the angular prolate spheroidal wave
functions of order 0, ps_n(x,c) and qs_n(x,c).  There is an implementation of the 
Xiao-Rokhlin algorithm, which is suitable for use when the bandlimit c and 
characteristic exponent n are relatively small, and a second algorithm which 
applies when 500 <= c <= 1,000,000 and n>=100 and runs in time independent of 
c and n.

The following files comprise the package:

1.  The file utils.f90 is a module containing simple utlity subroutines for 
printing, searching, sorting and the like.

2.  The file chebyshev.f90 is a module for forming and manipulating Chebyshev
expansions of univariate functions.

3.  The file tensor.f90 is a module for forming and manipulating bivariate
Chebyshev expansions of functions of two variables.

4.  The file adapquad.f90 is a module which contains primitive routines for 
adaptive Gaussian quadrature.

5.  The file create_boundchi.f90 contains a program which constructs a 
precomputed expansion used in prolates.f90 to bound the Sturm-Liouville eigenvalues
of the prolate spheroidal wave functions; this expansion is written to a fortran 
file called  boundchi.f90

  IMPORTANT NOTE: this code must be run using quadruple precision (REAL*16) 
  arithmetic

6.  The file prolates.f90 is a module for evaluating the prolate spheroidal
wave functions of order 0 using the Xiao-Rokhlin alorithm.

7.  The file linearode.f90 is a module which implements an adaptive spectral solver 
for second and third order linear ordinary differential equations.

8.  The file riccati.f90 is a module which contains an adaptive spectral solver for
the Riccati equation r'(t) + r(t)^2 + q(t) = 0.

9.  The file prolates_window.f90 contains code for applying the ``windowing 
algorithm'' so as to evaluate the nonoscillatory phase function for the spheroidal 
wave equation and its first few derivatives at the point 0

10.  The file prolates_exps.f90 contains code for constructing expansions of the
the Sturm-Liouville eigenvalue chi as a function of the bandlimit c and of a
parameter u related to the value of the nonoscillatory phase function at 0

11.  The file create_prolexps.f90 contains code for writing the expansions
generated by prolates_exps.f90 to the fortran file prolexps.f90 for use by 
prolates_fast.f90

  IMPORTANT NOTE: it is best to run this code using REAL*10 arithmetic, which
  ensures that the resulting expansions achieve double precision accurcy.
  When executed using REAL*8 arithemtic, roughly 11-12 digit accuracy is
  obtained instead.

12.  The file prolates_fast.f90 contains code for evaluating the angular prolate
spheroidal wave functions ps_n(x,c) and qs_n(x,c) in time independent of bandlimit
c and characteristic exponent n

