The following programs perform the numerical experiments described in the preprint

    Xinge Zhang and James Bremer, "An O(1) algorithm for the numerical evaluation
    of the prolate spheroidal wave functions of order 0".  arXiv:????.???

and produce the graphs contained therein:

13.  The file plot_chi.f90 contains a program for producing plots of chi as a
function of characteristic exponent and as a function of a multiple of the
value of the nonoscillatory phase function at 0 which appear as Figure 1.

14.  The file plot_A.f90 contains a program for producting the plos
of A_nu(\gamma^2) contained in Figure 2.

15.  The file plot_phase.f90 contains a program for producing the plots
of the derivatives of the phase functions which appear as Figure 3

16.  The file test_chiexp.f90 contains a program which tests the speed and
accuracy with which the  expansions in prolexps.f90 evaluate the
Sturm-Liouville eigenvalues via comparison with the Xiao-Rokhlin algorithm.
It produces the LaTeX source for a table presenting the results.

17.  The file test_pseval.f90 contains a program which tests the speed
and accuracy with which the code in prolates_fast.f90 evaluates ps_n(x,c)
via comparison with the Xiao-Rokhlin algorithm; it produces LaTeX code
for tables which display the results
